Scotia first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Scotia had a population of 681. The population density was {{convert|912.9|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Scotia was 474 (69.6%) [[White Americans|White]], 7 (1.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 27 (4.0%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 5 (0.7%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 2 (0.3%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 39 (5.7%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 127 (18.6%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 128 persons (18.8%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Scotia CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0670518 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 3, 2025}}</ref>

The census reported that 677 people (99.4% of the population) lived in households, 4 (0.6%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and no one was institutionalized.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 226 households, out of which 85 (37.6%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 98 (43.4%) were married-couple households, 31 (13.7%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 45 (19.9%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 52 (23.0%) had a male householder with no partner present. 45 households (19.9%) were one person, and 16 (7.1%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 3.0.<ref name=DP1/> There were 152 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (67.3% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Scotia CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0670518 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 3, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 222 people (32.6%) under the age of 18, 45 people (6.6%) aged 18 to 24, 203 people (29.8%) aged 25 to 44, 150 people (22.0%) aged 45 to 64, and 61 people (9.0%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 30.9{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 112.8 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 276 housing units at an average density of {{convert|370.0|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 226 (81.9%) were occupied. Of these, 86 (38.1%) were owner-occupied, and 140 (61.9%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

